    "recap_headline": "University of North Florida",
    "recap_text": "JACKSONVILLE, Fla.\u00a0-\nNorth Florida Baseball earned a walk-off victory in Game 1 of its series against FGCU, 5-4, at Harmon Stadium on Friday.\nThe Eagles scored two runs in the sixth inning and two in the seventh frame. However, North Florida fought back to plate five unanswered runs to win the game in its last two at bats.\nSophomore utility player\nSeth Alford\nbelted a three-run home run in the bottom of the eighth inning to cut North Florida's deficit to just one run.\nAlford came up again in the ninth frame and was hit by a pitch with the bases loaded to tie the game at four apiece. Redshirt sophomore outfielder\nCarter White\nworked a bases-loaded walk later in the frame to secure the walk-off win.\nNORTH FLORIDA 5, FGCU 4\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nDakota Stone\n(4-2)\nLoss:\nEvan Dempsey (3-1)\nLine Scores\nNORTH FLORIDA\n| 5 R, 4 H, 0 E\nFGCU\n| 4 R, 10 H, 0 E\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nSeth Alford\n| 1-3, 4 RBI, 1 HR, 1 R\nDakota Stone\n| 6.0 IP, 7 H, 2 R, 2 ER, 9 K, 2 BB\nFGCU\nEvan Dempsey | 3-4, 3 RBI, 1 HR, 1 R, 1 BB, 7.2 IP, 3 H, 3 R, 3 ER, 9 K, 1 BB\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida will return to Harmon Stadium for Game 2 against Florida Gulf Coast on Saturday, March 21 at 3:05 p.m. ET.",
